<h1>Homepage</h1>
<p><img src="/static/starry.png" alt="header" /></p>
<h3>About me</h3>
<p>This is my little sanctuary where I bottle up the unix computer zealot in me, you can call me <code>microsounds</code> if you want.</p>
<p>I like <del>muted pastels,</del> starry night skies, people watching and the <a href="http://markburgess.org/unix/unix.html">unix programming environment</a>.
I like to have <a href="https://effexxx.bandcamp.com/album/from-4jyo-han-to-everywhere-again">this album</a> in the background sometimes.</p>
<p>More importantly, I enjoy automating things in such a way that they can be left alone and never thought about again.
Sometimes, this is a never-ending process.</p>
<h3>Things I’ve made recently</h3>
<ul>
<li><em>(2019–present)</em> my “graphical shell” computing environment — <a href="/notes/dotfiles.htm"><code>microsounds/atelier</code></a>
<ul>
<li><em>My self-contained and unabridged collection of dotfiles and scripts for Debian GNU/Linux.</em></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><em>(2020–present)</em> static microblog processor in POSIX shell — <a href="https://github.com/microsounds/kagami"><code>microsounds/kagami</code></a>
<ul>
<li><em>A user-extensible macro preprocessor and generator for creating static webpages and blog sites.</em></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><em>(2019–present)</em> this website and it’s kagami template — <a href="https://github.com/microsounds/microsounds.github.io"><code>microsounds/microsounds.github.io</code></a></li>
</ul>
<h3>Old projects</h3>
<ul>
<li><em>(2016–2017)</em> <em><strong>[retired]</strong></em> lightweight futaba-like messageboard system in C — <a href="https://github.com/microsounds/akari-bbs"><code>microsounds/akari-bbs</code></a></li>
<li><em>(2016)</em> CPU-based tripcode generator for futaba-like imageboards — <a href="https://github.com/microsounds/tripforce"><code>microsounds/tripforce</code></a></li>
<li><em>(2016)</em> <em><strong>[retired]</strong></em> command-line utility for scraping Bandcamp albums — <a href="https://github.com/microsounds/bc-dl"><code>microsounds/bc-dl</code></a></li>
<li><em>(2016)</em> command-line stack-based RPN calculator — <a href="https://github.com/microsounds/hpsh"><code>microsounds/hpsh</code></a></li>
</ul>
<h3>Contact me</h3>
<p>If it’s about a project or an article on this website, feel free to open an issue or a pull request on Github.</p>
